<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9933> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9933" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/23> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "pp. 65-72" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6032> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6032" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Amit. (Q. P[-]), Degrassi 170f.; Fast. Amer., ibid. 242; Fast. Colot. (Q. Pedius Q. f.), ibid. 274f.; Fast. Mag. Vic., ibid. 282f.; cf. Act. Tr. for 45, ibid. 86f. with the filiation M. f., and discussion on p. 134. Octavian chose him to be his colleague (Vell. 2.65.2, and 69.5; Plin. NH 35.21; Tac. Dial. 17.1; App. BC 3.94; Dio 46.46.1; Zonar. 10.15). He carried the law providing for the prosecution of Caesar's murderers (Res Gest. D. Aug. 2; Liv. Per. 120; Vell. 2.69.5, lege Pedia; Suet. Nero 3.1; Galba 3.2; App. BC 3.95; 4.27; Dio 46.48, and 49.5; 47.22.4), and in Octavian's absence one rescinding the declarations of Antony and Lepidus as public enemies (App. BC 3.96; Dio 46.52.3-4). An old man, he died shortly before the arrival of the Triumvirs in Rome from the weariness and excitement that attended the first executions in the proscriptions (App. BC 4.6; Dio 47.15.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5921> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5921" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate under Caesar in Spain (Bell. Hisp. 2.2; 12.2; Dio 43.42.1; see 46. Legates. and above, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5898> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5898" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He celebrated a triumph pro consule ex Hispania on December 13, but according to Dio, illegally, since he had only been one of Caesar's Legates (Act. Tr., Degrassi 86f., 567; Plin. NH 35.21; Dio 43.31.1, and 42.1). See below, Legates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5846> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5846" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate of Caesar, who was sent in advance to Spain, along with Q. Fabius Maximus (Bell. Hisp. 2.2; 12.2; Dio 43.31.3; cf. 43.42.1, and Act. Tr. for 45)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5631> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5631" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Crushed Milo's revolt near Cosa (Caes. BC 3.22)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5163> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5163" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate under Caesar in Gaul (see 57, Legates; cf. Cic. Planc. 17). See D.-G. 3.700." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5105> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5105" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate of Caesar in Gaul (Caes. BG 2.2.1, and 11.3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5065> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5065" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legates under Caesar in Gaul. The four unnamed Legates in Caesar's battle with Ariovistus probably were among these (BG 1.52. 1). See 57, Legates; and esp. D.-G. 3.696ff." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10177> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10177" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Hispania. MRR II.309, Itgenshorst no. 268, Rich no. 269." .
